result.execSummary:
The defendant Salena Jean Miller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Salena Jean Miller is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Salena Jean Miller was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Fox, ADA:  Alexis McKinley, DF ATTY:  Lida Marie Bannink, DF:  Salena Jean Miller appeared from jail. Includes 14CF192, 14CF213 and 14CM205. Defendant wishes to be sentenced today. Def has been incarcerated since November 19, 2014. There is not revocation paperwork filed. The defendant wishes to revoke herself. Attorney Bannink updates the court on def status. Atty Bannink questions def regarding refusing the balance of probation. ADA McKinley states def may have charges in Pierce County but notes she has not been charged yet. Court takes a recess to allow Attorney's to contact Pierce County. Back on at 9:40 am. Atty's were unable to get a definitive answer whether or not she will be charged. Court finds def freely, voluntarily and knowingly refuses balance of probation. Court grants motion. Sentencing recommendations. Court orders: 
- 14CF192 ct 2: $243.00 court costs; 30 days (concurrent to 14CF213 and 14CM205)

- 14CF213 ct 3: $243.00 court costs; 6 months in St. Croix County Jail, with good time. With credit for 106 days for time served. 

- 14CM205 ct 1: $243.00 court costs; 5 months in St. Croix County Jail consecutive to 14CF213, with good time.

Court directs the Clerk of Court to enter a civil money judgment for court costs.
Defendant is advised of right to appeal.
